This paper is focused on the identification of malware tasks, which is a key aspect of cybersecurity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which suggests it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of sparse training data, which could place it in cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
